Thirty three children were hospitalised after showing signs of respiratory distress while swimming at Zoo Lake JOHANNESBURG Paramedics say about 30 children have been hospitalised and assessed for toxic fume inhalation.Netcare 911 says a four-month-old baby was among the children who were transported to hospital after allegedly inhaling acid from a swimming pool at Zoo Lake yesterday.The children were taken to hospital after experiencing respiratory distress and no fatalities have been reported.Netcare 911's Athlenda Mathe said, The children showed signs of respiratory distress, some were even vomiting. _EDITOR S NOTE: Paramedics earlier reported that 33 children were involved in the incident but Community Development MMC Nonhlanhla Sifumba has subsequently clarified that only 20 children were affected. _